The paper presents a new data structure for multidimensional data, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The focus on data structures and algorithms for efficient insertion, deletion, and queries suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The mention of range queries and approximate queries suggests that it could also belong to cs.DB (Databases) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the mention of R^2 and R^d suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) if the multidimensional data is image data.
